                +tex.
                    $\mathbf{Definition}$ (Homogeneous structure).
                    A type $A$ is homogeneous, if there are terms of the following types:
                    i) $e:A$; ii) $t: \prod_{x:A} A = A$; iii) $p: \prod_{x:A}t_x(e) = x$.

                +code.
                    def ‚àû-unital-magma (X : U) :=
                    Œ£ (e : X) (Œº : X ‚Üí X ‚Üí X), Œ† (x : X),
                      Path X (Œº e x) x √ó Path X (Œº x e) x

                    def is-left-invertible (X : U) (M : ‚àû-unital-magma X) :=
                    Œ† (a : X), isEquiv X X (Œª (x : X), M.Œº x a)

                    def H-space := Œ£ (X : U), ‚àû-unital-magma X
